                                                                                                                                  "type": "tool_result",
                                                                                                                                  "tool_use_id": "toolu_01F1RCDtPd46rScRr8UnbMQz",
                                                                                                                                  "content": "\n        ============================= test session starts =============================\n        platform win32 -- Python 3.12.9, pytest-7.3.1, pluggy-1.5.0 -- C:\\Users\\benbu\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312-arm64\\python.exe\n        cachedir: .pytest_cache\n        rootdir: C:\\Users\\benbu\\Code\\llm-utilities-git\\bots\n        configfile: pytest.ini\n        plugins: anyio-4.8.0, langsmith-0.3.8, cov-6.0.0, timeout-2.4.0\n        timeout: 10.0s\n        timeout method: thread\n        timeout func_only: False\n        collecting ... collected 1 item\n        tests/test_python_edit.py::test_tokenize_basic FAILED                    [100%]\n        ================================== FAILURES ===================================\n        _____________________________ test_tokenize_basic _____________________________\n            def test_tokenize_basic():\n                \"\"\"Test basic tokenization of comments and strings\"\"\"\n                source = '\\n    # Header comment\\n    x = \"string literal\"  # Inline comment\\n    y = 1\\n    '\n                tokenized, token_map = tokenize_source(source)\n                assert '# Header comment' not in tokenized\n                assert '\"string literal\"' not in tokenized\n        >       assert '# Inline comment' not in tokenized\n        E       AssertionError: assert '# Inline comment' not in '\\n    __TOK... y = 1\\n    '\n        E         '# Inline comment' is contained here:\n        E           \n        E               __TOKEN__232048656164657220636f6d6d656e74__\n        E               x = __TOKEN__22737472696e67206c69746572616c22__  # Inline comment\n        E         ?                                                      ++++++++++++++++\n        E               y = 1\n        tests\\test_python_edit.py:448: AssertionError\n        =========================== short test summary info ===========================\n        FAILED tests/test_python_edit.py::test_tokenize_basic - AssertionError: asser...\n        ============================== 1 failed in 1.03s =============================="
                                                                                                                                 }
                                                                                                                                ],
                                                                                                                                "node_class": "AnthropicNode",
                                                                                                                                "replies": [
                                                                                                                                 {
                                                                                                                                  "content": "Great! The timeout is fixed. Now the test is failing because the inline comment `# Inline comment` is not being tokenized. Looking at the code, I can see why:\n\nAt line 378-385, there's code to handle inline comments (comments that appear after code on the same line), but it only runs if:\n1. `'#'` is in `processed_line` \n2. AND `not contains_token(processed_line)`\n\nBut in our case, `processed_line` already contains a token (`__TOKEN__22737472696e67206c69746572616c22__` for the string), so `contains_token(processed_line)` returns `True`, and the inline comment handling is skipped.\n\nLet me fix this by adjusting the logic:",
                                                                                                                                  "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                  "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                  "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                   {
                                                                                                                                    "type": "tool_use",
                                                                                                                                    "id": "toolu_01RNBg3miJusvtFudVXyAXmD",
                                                                                                                                    "name": "patch_edit",
                                                                                                                                    "input": {
                                                                                                                                     "file_path": "bots/tools/python_edit.py",
                                                                                                                                     "patch_content": "\n                        --- \n                        +++ \n                        @@ -376,7 +376,8 @@\n                                             processed_line = processed_line[:match.start()] + hex_val + processed_line[match.end():]\n                                             token_counter += 1\n                                     if '#' in processed_line and (not contains_token(processed_line)):\n                        -                comment_start = processed_line.index('#')\n                        +                # Find the first # that's not inside a token\n                        +                comment_start = processed_line.find('#')\n                                         code = processed_line[:comment_start]\n                                         comment = processed_line[comment_start:]\n                                         token_name, hex_val = create_token(comment, token_counter, current_hash)"
                                                                                                                                    }
                                                                                                                                   }
                                                                                                                                  ],
                                                                                                                                  "tool_results": [],
                                                                                                                                  "node_class": "AnthropicNode",
                                                                                                                                  "replies": [
                                                                                                                                   {
                                                                                                                                    "content": "ok",
                                                                                                                                    "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                    "role": "user",
                                                                                                                                    "tool_calls": [],
                                                                                                                                    "tool_results": [
                                                                                                                                     {
                                                                                                                                      "type": "tool_result",
                                                                                                                                      "tool_use_id": "toolu_01RNBg3miJusvtFudVXyAXmD",
                                                                                                                                      "content": "\n        Successfully applied patches:\n        Note: Applied hunk starting with                      at line 376 (different from specified line 375), and had to ignore whitespace to find match"
                                                                                                                                     }
                                                                                                                                    ],
                                                                                                                                    "node_class": "AnthropicNode",
                                                                                                                                    "replies": [
                                                                                                                                     {
                                                                                                                                      "content": "Actually, that won't fix it. The issue is the condition `not contains_token(processed_line)`. We need to handle inline comments even when the line contains tokens. Let me fix this properly:",
                                                                                                                                      "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                      "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                      "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                       {
